page.title: 02FAMILY LIFE
page.content: My name is Tracy Goode, I am 11. I got up this morning, 5th June 1985, and went downstairs to drink some coffee. I went through to the bedroom and washed myself. I went upstairs and got my pink pants, white and yellow socks, blue jumper and skirt. For breakfast I had cereal. I then started to walk to school. The bell went at 9 a.m. Samantha and I went in the hall for assembly. We then had maths. At 10.30 the bell went for first break. I went outside for a game with Samantha and Ruth. We did a couple of English exercises after going back into school. After that I had my dinner. At 1 p.m. the bell went and we had to go in and do maps. At 2 p.m. the bell rang and we went outside and played. After an hour the bell went for hometime. I got my bag and bike and rode home. I went to bed at 9 p.m.
